WEBVTT

00:01.016 --> 00:03.084
Clarence:
Previously on "Clarence"...

00:03.086 --> 00:04.085
Sumo's family lived
in a hole in the ground,

00:04.087 --> 00:05.787
like a bunch of snakes.

00:05.789 --> 00:07.856
Oh, and Sumo had
a little badger friend!

00:07.858 --> 00:09.190
I think it was a badger.

00:09.192 --> 00:10.925
Anyway, the sky got real mad,

00:10.927 --> 00:13.027
and it took Sumo's
new badger friend away.

00:13.029 --> 00:15.263
And that's when Sumo's family
got serious.

00:15.265 --> 00:17.933
[ Singing dramatic music ]

00:20.437 --> 00:21.436
[ Remote clicks ]

00:21.438 --> 00:23.605
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:26.110 --> 00:29.444
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:29.446 --> 00:31.446
[ Thunder rumbles ]

00:31.448 --> 00:34.950
[ Wind howling ]

00:41.358 --> 00:42.524
[ Chittering ]

00:42.526 --> 00:44.826
Looking pretty hairy out there,
Noles.

00:44.828 --> 00:46.794
We might be in it
for the long haul.

00:46.796 --> 00:48.363
Just be me, you...

00:48.365 --> 00:49.998
and your precious
little prank!

00:50.000 --> 00:51.799
Let's just go
to another room.

00:51.801 --> 00:53.901
Just like you
to skirt the law.

00:53.903 --> 00:57.372
The rules say that we serve
detention here, and here only!

00:57.374 --> 01:00.008
What kind of disciplinarian
would I be

01:00.010 --> 01:02.310
if I let a misconduct
of this stature slip by?

01:02.312 --> 01:04.145
[ Snickers ]
- Oh, no.

01:04.147 --> 01:06.414
Nothing slips past
old Reese the Beast!

01:06.416 --> 01:08.983
Oh, yeah?
Well, who's that outside?

01:08.985 --> 01:10.651
What?!
Where?!

01:10.653 --> 01:13.155
Hmm?
I ain't see nothing.

01:13.890 --> 01:14.890
What the...

01:14.892 --> 01:15.891
[ Creak! ]

01:15.893 --> 01:17.826
[ Grunting ]

01:17.828 --> 01:20.161
Oh.
- [ Laughing ]

01:20.163 --> 01:22.264
Belson!
That's not funny!

01:23.867 --> 01:26.001
Oh!
[ Sputters ]

01:26.003 --> 01:28.036
We'll see who's laughing
when you're held back.

01:28.038 --> 01:29.871
Wait, what?
You can't do that!

01:29.873 --> 01:30.905
Those aren't the rules!

01:30.907 --> 01:32.107
Detentions add up.

01:32.109 --> 01:33.675
[ Laughs ]
[ Electricity crackles ]

01:34.745 --> 01:35.911
Power outage?
Flooding?

01:35.913 --> 01:37.212
We got to get to the gym!

01:37.214 --> 01:39.681
The gym is the designated
safety zone

01:39.683 --> 01:40.915
in an emergency.

01:40.917 --> 01:42.950
It's all
gonna be fine...

01:42.952 --> 01:44.920
as soon as we get inside.

01:44.922 --> 01:46.722
No, that's, my...
Ah, come on.

01:46.724 --> 01:48.890
Where the, uh...

01:48.892 --> 01:50.759
Oh, come on.

01:50.761 --> 01:52.227
Belson, that's illegal.

01:52.229 --> 01:53.795
Oh, look.
It's open.

01:53.797 --> 01:55.230
Hey!
- What's going on out here?!

01:55.232 --> 01:56.698
We have citizens here

01:56.700 --> 01:59.534
who require access
to the emergency safety zone.

01:59.536 --> 02:01.570
What the heck
is on your face, Jim?

02:01.572 --> 02:03.972
Brenda, you just gotta let us in!
Says who?

02:03.974 --> 02:07.108
The school safety officer --
Miss Baker!

02:07.110 --> 02:08.876
Well,
- she's not here right now.

02:08.878 --> 02:09.878
Melanie?

02:09.880 --> 02:11.880
So I guess that means...

02:11.882 --> 02:13.248
I'm in charge!

02:13.250 --> 02:15.717
Can we please come in?

02:15.719 --> 02:17.785
It's so rainy
out there.

02:17.787 --> 02:18.820
[ Sneezes ]

02:18.822 --> 02:20.055
Ugh, fine!

02:20.057 --> 02:21.122
Go, go, go, go, go!

02:21.124 --> 02:22.123
And, uh, you two, uh...

02:22.125 --> 02:23.425
Don't worry, Brenda.

02:23.427 --> 02:25.894
We'll do whatever it takes
to find Melanie.

02:25.896 --> 02:27.329
Oh, yeah, yeah.

02:27.331 --> 02:28.730
Go look for Miss Baker.
That's your assignment.

02:28.732 --> 02:30.131
[ Chuckles ]

02:30.133 --> 02:31.599
But you're gonna need
an extra tank of gas.

02:31.601 --> 02:32.668
For what?

02:32.670 --> 02:33.801
For the storm!

02:33.803 --> 02:35.236
Come on, Belson!
Shake a leg!

02:35.238 --> 02:37.272
Adults are so useless.

02:37.274 --> 02:41.243
Ha! Dingus and McNobrain
on the case.

02:42.078 --> 02:43.078
Whoa!
[ Body thuds ]

02:43.080 --> 02:44.679
[ Laughs ]

02:44.681 --> 02:45.813
[ Upbeat music plays ]

02:45.815 --> 02:47.448
[ Flatly ]
Oh, no, are you okay?

02:47.450 --> 02:50.585
[ Scoffs ] You don't care about
anyone or anything, do ya?

02:50.587 --> 02:52.921
Everything's just
a big joke to you.

02:52.923 --> 02:55.690
[ Scoffs ] What do you care
about? Rules?

02:55.692 --> 02:57.258
Yeah, yeah, that...

02:57.260 --> 02:58.760
and so much more.

02:58.762 --> 03:00.161
[ Sniffles ]

03:00.163 --> 03:02.464
Gross. Why don't we just go
to her house, then?

03:02.466 --> 03:05.934
I...don't know
where that is.

03:05.936 --> 03:07.168
Never been invited.
[ Rustling ]

03:07.170 --> 03:09.137
Belson,
- that is personal property!

03:09.139 --> 03:12.040
Well, I already found it,
so we might as well use it.

03:12.042 --> 03:13.942
Oh. A clue.

03:13.944 --> 03:16.945
Uh, back up.

03:16.947 --> 03:18.546
A little more.

03:18.548 --> 03:19.948
A little more.

03:19.950 --> 03:21.482
A little more.

03:21.484 --> 03:22.784
Hmm.

03:22.786 --> 03:25.019
A little mo-- - Ugh.
It's her address!

03:25.021 --> 03:26.888
Now,
we can go there already?

03:26.890 --> 03:28.489
Ah.
Good idea.

03:28.491 --> 03:30.124
♪♪

03:30.126 --> 03:31.693
Let's ride.

03:33.730 --> 03:35.297
Huh?
What was that?

03:35.299 --> 03:37.699
Ugh.
Maybe I should drive.

03:37.701 --> 03:39.066
What are you, loco?

03:39.068 --> 03:41.636
Come on.
Look at my score.

03:41.638 --> 03:42.637
Trust me.

03:42.639 --> 03:44.739
[ Game chiming ]
I guess I have to.

03:44.741 --> 03:45.974
♪♪

03:45.976 --> 03:47.809
[ Tires squeal ]

03:47.811 --> 03:48.976
[ Chuckles ]

03:48.978 --> 03:51.245
Oh, no!
Oh, look out!

03:51.247 --> 03:53.648
Don't hit her!
Try to stay on the road!

03:53.650 --> 03:55.150
Oh, sick!

03:56.820 --> 03:58.920
Not a bad trick, Belson.

03:58.922 --> 04:00.822
[ Flashlights click ]

04:00.824 --> 04:02.490
Dang.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.091
She must've
gotten robbed.

04:04.093 --> 04:05.160
Robbed?

04:05.162 --> 04:06.260
Let's split up.

04:06.262 --> 04:08.396
Tactical sweep.
Good idea.

04:08.398 --> 04:09.430
Hmm.

04:09.432 --> 04:11.332
These fingerprints look fresh.

04:11.334 --> 04:13.168
That can only mean
- that someone has been here.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.736
Hmm.
- Was there a struggle, perhaps?

04:14.738 --> 04:15.736
Fisticuffs?

04:15.738 --> 04:16.604
Lisa:<i> Hey, Melly!</i>

04:16.606 --> 04:18.406
<i>Me and Mackenzie can't wait</i>

04:18.408 --> 04:20.174
<i>for you to be a west coast</i>
<i>sunshine babe with us!</i>

04:20.176 --> 04:22.277
<i>Bring your bikini, LOL!</i>

04:22.279 --> 04:24.712
<i>Whoo!</i>
<i>You're moving to California!</i>

04:24.714 --> 04:26.447
<i>Hearts, Lisa.</i>

04:26.449 --> 04:28.883
<i>P.S. -- You're moving</i>
<i>to California.</i>

04:28.885 --> 04:29.918
Oh, man.

04:29.920 --> 04:32.887
Melanie.
Melanie?

04:32.889 --> 04:35.023
Melanie.

04:35.025 --> 04:37.024
Belson,
did you find anything yet?

04:37.026 --> 04:39.594
Uh, nah.
It's nothing.

04:39.596 --> 04:42.531
Look, it's after 5:00,
so I think I'm gonna go home.

04:42.533 --> 04:45.600
You're leaving?
We're about to crack this case!

04:45.602 --> 04:47.602
You got it.
Keep looking, Reese.

04:47.604 --> 04:49.237
You'll find her
someday.

04:49.239 --> 04:52.374
That's right.
Turn around, quitter!

04:52.376 --> 04:56.444
There goes Belson "too cool
for everyone at school" Noles.

04:56.446 --> 04:57.545
What?

04:57.547 --> 04:58.613
Shut up.

04:58.615 --> 05:01.316
He doesn't care
- about nothing or nobody.

05:01.318 --> 05:04.286
and nobody cares about him.

05:04.288 --> 05:07.088
You know I was trying
to be nice, but you know what?

05:07.090 --> 05:08.723
Here!

05:08.725 --> 05:12.160
Uh, I think this paper
has words on it.

05:12.162 --> 05:14.896
Are you kidding?
Miss Baker's gone.

05:14.898 --> 05:16.564
She's moving to California.

05:16.566 --> 05:18.733
If you were even half the cop
you pretend to be,

05:18.735 --> 05:20.668
you could have
figured it out by now.

05:20.670 --> 05:22.904
I did,
- and I'm literally a child!

05:22.906 --> 05:25.473
You're dumber than a child!

05:25.475 --> 05:27.408
What?

05:27.410 --> 05:29.277
She's moving,
- and she didn't say nothing?

05:29.279 --> 05:33.614
[ Crying ]

05:33.616 --> 05:34.916
Melanie.

05:34.918 --> 05:38.953
I'm sorry, Belson.
- Lots of people care about you.

05:38.955 --> 05:40.488
I'm the fool!

05:40.490 --> 05:43.024
I'm the fool
of the whole town!

05:43.026 --> 05:45.093
Uh, come on, man.

05:45.095 --> 05:46.327
Stop crying.

05:46.329 --> 05:47.595
You're not a fool.

05:47.597 --> 05:49.931
[ Sobs ]
I'm not?!

05:49.933 --> 05:51.432
[ Sniffles ]

05:51.434 --> 05:55.770
Well, tell me something
that's good about me.

05:55.772 --> 05:57.138
Uh, g-- g--

05:57.140 --> 06:00.942
Uh, you've got a nice...
mustache.

06:00.944 --> 06:02.544
Thank you for that.

06:02.546 --> 06:04.779
But it doesn't matter now.

06:04.781 --> 06:06.114
Melanie's long gone.

06:06.116 --> 06:07.382
To get to California,

06:07.384 --> 06:09.684
we'd need a whole extra
tank of gas.

06:09.686 --> 06:10.818
[ Gasps ]

06:10.820 --> 06:17.459
You're gonna need
an extra tank of gas.

06:18.462 --> 06:19.460
Shoop!          Shoop!

06:19.462 --> 06:21.362
Mr. Reese: Aw, Melanie,

06:21.364 --> 06:24.198
I hope you're happy,
whoever you're with.

06:24.200 --> 06:26.034
[ Thunder cracks ]

06:26.036 --> 06:27.802
-Clarence?
-Clarence?!

06:27.804 --> 06:30.171
-Clarence?
-I don't think he's in there.

06:30.173 --> 06:31.806
Yeah, looks closed.

06:31.808 --> 06:34.042
But Clarence said he'd bring me
a raisin slurpy drink,

06:34.044 --> 06:36.878
and Rough Riders is the only
place that serves it.

06:36.880 --> 06:38.312
The only place.

06:38.314 --> 06:39.914
Um...
Oh, I'm sure of it.

06:39.916 --> 06:42.917
Come on, buddy!
- Are you in one of those tubes?!

06:42.919 --> 06:44.085
Clarence!

06:44.087 --> 06:45.487
Puppet Clarence: Jeff. - Huh?

06:45.489 --> 06:47.421
You'll never find me.

06:47.423 --> 06:49.157
I'm gone for good.

06:49.159 --> 06:50.424
Thanks a lot, Jeff.

06:50.426 --> 06:53.161
C-C-Clare--
Clarence?

06:53.163 --> 06:54.162
Jeff?

06:54.164 --> 06:55.997
Oh! Aah! Aah!

06:55.999 --> 06:57.999
Oh!

06:58.001 --> 07:00.201
[ Water bubbling ]

07:00.203 --> 07:01.403
[ All gasp ]

07:01.405 --> 07:03.205
Percy: Heeeeeeeelp!

07:03.207 --> 07:04.439
-What?
-Oh!

07:04.441 --> 07:06.007
-Oh, Percy!
-Hold on there, buddy!

07:06.009 --> 07:09.010
Come here, I got ya! Come on.
[ Car crashes ]

07:09.012 --> 07:10.878
Need a lift?

07:10.880 --> 07:12.180
[ Upbeat music plays ]

07:12.182 --> 07:14.415
[ Wind whistles ]

07:14.417 --> 07:17.852
[ Grunts ]
- Shoop, we're on to your lies!

07:17.854 --> 07:19.754
You're going down!

07:19.756 --> 07:20.555
Hmm?           Hmm?

07:20.557 --> 07:24.092
I ain't going nowhere.

07:24.094 --> 07:25.226
[ Grunts ]

07:25.228 --> 07:26.795
[ Buzzer ]

07:26.797 --> 07:29.397
Oh, good shot!

07:30.534 --> 07:33.300
Has anyone seen Clarence?
Is he here?

07:33.302 --> 07:35.536
You four,
get in the corner!

07:35.538 --> 07:36.771
Corner?
- Yes, ma'am!

07:36.773 --> 07:37.939
Are you serious?

07:37.941 --> 07:40.875
You two, my office, now.

07:40.877 --> 07:42.410
[ Generator whirs,
radio static crackles ]

07:42.412 --> 07:44.879
Dingus and McNobrain.
[ Chuckles ]

07:44.881 --> 07:46.881
I never thought
you'd figure it out.

07:46.883 --> 07:49.317
You knew about Miss Baker
the whole time,

07:49.319 --> 07:51.286
you sent us
on a wild goose chase,

07:51.288 --> 07:52.620
and on top of everything,

07:52.622 --> 07:54.756
you're jailing citizens
in a storm?!

07:54.758 --> 07:57.224
Um, are these beans
up for grabs?

07:57.226 --> 07:59.226
No!
- Why'd you do it?

07:59.228 --> 08:00.895
Isn't it obvious?

08:00.897 --> 08:03.230
For the love of the game.

08:03.232 --> 08:07.568
[ Hip-hop music plays ]

08:07.570 --> 08:09.771
I needed some me time,
and I wasn't about to let

08:09.773 --> 08:12.006
a bit of drizzle ruin
my b-ball sesh.

08:12.008 --> 08:13.741
I knew Melanie had split
for the coast,

08:13.743 --> 08:15.310
so I had to get you
out of my hair,

08:15.312 --> 08:17.245
knowing there was no way
you'd find her.

08:17.247 --> 08:18.813
But without
our safety officer,

08:18.815 --> 08:21.749
all those people are gonna
be out there in the flood.

08:21.751 --> 08:22.917
Good.

08:22.919 --> 08:24.819
You're a sick pup.

08:24.821 --> 08:27.422
I'm in here every day
after school!

08:27.424 --> 08:29.490
Nobody else even uses this gym!

08:29.492 --> 08:30.825
It's mine!

08:30.827 --> 08:33.261
It's my gym, and I'll do
what I want with it!

08:33.263 --> 08:35.596
You can't get away
with this.

08:35.598 --> 08:38.432
Actually, she can.

08:38.434 --> 08:39.500
Belson?

08:39.502 --> 08:41.035
[ Chuckles ]
That's right.

08:41.037 --> 08:43.170
Dingus here
gave me a little call

08:43.172 --> 08:45.039
to tell me you were on your way.

08:45.041 --> 08:46.507
We made a little agreement.

08:46.509 --> 08:49.376
He'll keep you out of my biz,
and in exchange,

08:49.378 --> 08:52.280
I'll wipe
his detention record clean.

08:52.282 --> 08:54.448
-Oh, my!
-This is getting good!

08:54.450 --> 08:57.351
Is this true?
- After all we've been through?

08:57.353 --> 09:00.054
Sorry, Reese,
but she's -- she's gone.

09:00.056 --> 09:02.957
I ain't wasting no more time
in detentions.

09:02.959 --> 09:05.059
[ Laughs ]

09:05.061 --> 09:07.361
Miss Baker:<i> Hello?</i>
<i>Is anyone out there!</i>

09:07.363 --> 09:09.731
<i>Attention, Aberdale residents,</i>
<i>this is Melanie Baker.</i>

09:09.733 --> 09:12.333
Melanie?!
Miss Baker's still here?!

09:12.335 --> 09:13.801
That's not possible!

09:13.803 --> 09:15.002
Huh?            Huh?

09:15.004 --> 09:16.637
[<i> Continues speaking</i>
<i>indistinctly</i> ]

09:16.639 --> 09:18.807
[ Bodies thud ]

09:18.809 --> 09:20.208
No, no!
Go away!

09:20.210 --> 09:21.208
We had a deal!

09:21.210 --> 09:22.243
The deal's off, you liar!

09:22.245 --> 09:24.411
Keep away!
Keep away!

09:24.413 --> 09:27.048
Come on!
Give it here!

09:27.050 --> 09:28.049
[ Grunts ]

09:28.051 --> 09:29.818
Oh. Oh, no!

09:31.988 --> 09:33.321
Ow!

09:33.323 --> 09:34.489
[ All gasp ]

09:34.491 --> 09:35.556
What? Foul!
That was a foul!

09:35.558 --> 09:36.991
[ Chuckles ]

09:36.993 --> 09:39.860
Did she get away?
- Not yet.

09:39.862 --> 09:41.229
Let's ride.

09:41.231 --> 09:42.730
Say what?

09:42.732 --> 09:44.331
Ooh!

09:44.333 --> 09:45.767
Aah! Ooh! [ Grunts ]

09:45.769 --> 09:48.169
Oh!
[ Panting ]

09:49.773 --> 09:51.205
What?!
[ Grunts ]

09:51.207 --> 09:53.107
♪♪

09:53.109 --> 09:55.910
She's getting away!
I can't see her.

09:55.912 --> 09:57.012
Later, chumps!

09:57.914 --> 10:00.248
That would have
come in handy earlier.

10:00.250 --> 10:01.682
It's up to you.

10:01.684 --> 10:02.516
Hmm.

10:02.518 --> 10:03.551
A little higher...

10:03.553 --> 10:04.852
and fire!

10:04.854 --> 10:05.753
[ Grunts ]

10:05.755 --> 10:07.522
Huh?
[ Grunts ]

10:07.524 --> 10:09.023
[ Cart crashes ]

10:09.025 --> 10:10.458
Throw me.

10:12.229 --> 10:14.028
You can do it.

10:14.030 --> 10:15.029
Hmm.

10:15.031 --> 10:17.899
[ Grunts ]

10:22.905 --> 10:24.872
Nooooo!

10:24.874 --> 10:27.541
Sorry, Brenda.
- I guess it's like they say --

10:27.543 --> 10:29.544
bad boys die hard.

10:29.546 --> 10:30.778
[ Sunglasses clatter ]

10:30.780 --> 10:32.713
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:32.715 --> 10:34.815
Don't worry.
We'll find him.

10:34.817 --> 10:36.317
<i>Uh, is anyone out there?</i>

10:36.319 --> 10:38.452
<i>Me, and several other citizens</i>
<i>are trapped</i>

10:38.454 --> 10:40.822
<i>inside 6400 North Adobe Way.</i>

10:40.824 --> 10:43.057
<i>Okay? 6400.</i>
You know that address?

10:43.059 --> 10:44.058
You bet I do.

10:44.060 --> 10:45.226
Let's ride.

10:45.228 --> 10:47.595
♪ Bad dudes ♪

10:47.597 --> 10:48.662
♪<i> Working as a team</i> ♪

10:48.664 --> 10:50.064
You know it is after 5:00.

10:50.066 --> 10:52.566
I could drop you off at home
if you want.

10:52.568 --> 10:54.635
Ha!
Not a chance, partner.

10:54.637 --> 10:56.604
We ride hard,

10:56.606 --> 10:59.140
we die ha--

10:59.142 --> 11:00.741
Whoa!
- Aah!

11:00.743 --> 11:02.177
[ Upbeat music plays ]

11:03.578 --> 11:05.413
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:06.949 --> 11:09.250
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.520 --> 11:13.254
♪ Picking my nose ♪
